Package: CppODE
Title: Automated 'C++' Code Generation for ODE Integration with Sensitivity Analysis
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Simon", "Beyer", , "simon.beyer@fdm.uni-freiburg.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Generates, compiles, and runs 'C++' solvers for systems of ordinary
    differential equations. Includes a variable-order BDF integrator with
    LAPACK/KLU linear algebra and a Rosenbrock4 method derived from
    'Boost.Numeric.Odeint'. First- and second-order parameter sensitivities are
    computed automatically via forward-mode automatic differentiation using the
    'FADBAD++' library. Supports time-based and root-triggered events, symbolic
    Jacobian generation, and sparse matrix factorization for large systems.
Language: en-US
License: MIT + file LICENSE
SystemRequirements: C++17; Python (>= 3.8) with SymPy; optional system
    libraries, detected by ./configure at install time:
    SUNDIALS (>= 6.0) for the CVODE() backend (libsundials-dev on
    Debian/Ubuntu, sundials-devel on Fedora, sundials via Homebrew on
    macOS); SuiteSparse / KLU for the sparse Jacobian path of both
    CppODE() and CVODE() (libsuitesparse-dev / suitesparse-devel /
    suite-sparse). Missing libraries don't prevent install — the
    affected features error cleanly at runtime with install hints.
Encoding: UTF-8
